comments: After Davis (LAL) disengages from Jokic (DEN), he establishes himself in a legal screening position in Grant's (DEN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Jokic (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Caruso (LAL).
Davis (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position in the post, while Caldwell-Pope (LAL) makes illegal contact to Jokic's (DEN) arm.
Jokic (DEN) makes marginal contact with Davis (LAL) as the two engage off-ball.
Davis (LAL) establishes himself in a legal screening position in Craig's (DEN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Jokic (DEN) makes marginal contact with his resting hand to James' (LAL) body during his driving shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in Bradley's (LAL) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bradley (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position during Grant's (DEN) shot attempt near the basket.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position as he contests Harris' (DEN) driving shot attempt.
James (LAL) receives the inbound pass and establishes his left foot as his pivot foot.  He then lifts his pivot foot to start his dribble.
Caruso (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Grant's (DEN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Craig (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by James (LAL).
Millsap (DEN) makes marginal contact to Davis' (LAL) back during the rebound, but the contact does not affect his ability to get to the ball as the clock expires.
Howard (LAL) never fully establishes himself in a legal screening position and delivers contact to Craig (DEN) that affects his ability to defend.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) makes marginal contact to Harris' (DEN) body at the start of the drive, but the contact does not affect his SQBR.
Howard (LAL) and Jokic (DEN) briefly engage and separate during the rebound, but the contact does not affect his ability to retrieve the ball.
Jokic (DEN) delivers contact to Howard's (LAL) back while simultaneously clamping his left arm and the contact affects his ability to rebound the ball.
Howard (LAL) has a resting hand on Murray (DEN) that he does not extend or apply force with during his driving shot attempt.  Howard legally contests the shot on his block attempt.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) and Jokic (DEN) make marginal contact as they briefly engage and separate during the rebound.
Grant (DEN) makes contact to Davis' (LAL) body that affects his SQBR.
Caruso (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in Millsap's (DEN) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Millsap (DEN) faces up with Davis (LAL) while grabbing his arm with two hands and the contact affects his ability to go for the rebound.
A timeout is whistled before any contact between Davis (LAL) and Grant (DEN).
James (LAL) makes marginal contact with Jokic's (DEN) at the start of the drive, but the contact does not affect his ability to start his dribble and path to the basket.
James (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact with a collapsed forearm during the driving shot attempt by Jokic (DEN).
James' (LAL) elbow makes contact to Jokic's (DEN) face during the rebound and the contact dislodges him.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in a screening position in Caruso's (LAL) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Caruso (LAL) is still moving laterally as he slides in front of Jokic (DEN) and makes contact to his body that affects his SQBR.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) places a resting hand on Murray's (DEN) hip during the inbound, but the contact does not affect his FOM.
Harris (DEN) commits a take foul on Davis (LAL).
